= Introduction ===================

A simple GEM plane of 1mx1m square to be used for solid_gemc simulation

The GEM plane construction assume SoLID GEM design, refer to 
https://hallaweb.jlab.org/wiki/index.php/Solid_GEM_Digitization#GEM_module.27s_geometry_and_material
https://hallaweb.jlab.org/wiki/index.php/Solid_GEM_Digitization#GEM_response

The output of the simulation can be used for digitization program

= how to use it ===================
you need to have solid software installed and "solid_gemc" compiled, refer 
https://hallaweb.jlab.org/wiki/index.php/Solid_Software

(prepare env)
source your_set_solid_script  

(interactive mode to see the setup)
solid_gemc UVatest_gem.gcard  

(batch mode to produce output file)
solid_gemc UVatest_gem.gcard -N=1e3 -OUTPUT="evio,output.evio" -USE_GUI=0 

(convert evio file to root file)
evio2root -INPUTF=output.evio -B="UVatest_gem"

(edit geometry in perl script and generate new setup)
./UVatest_gem.pl config_UVatest_gem.dat

=  note ===================

To edit geometry, change running condition, and understanding tree content in root file,
refer to general note 
https://eic.jlab.org/wiki/index.php/Detector_simulation_general_note

